{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CXJAvFdEhh2iKJpSrDpA7C","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Beb4TbnUESNeUmKMEDYctf","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Investigate watch cache DELETE event bug","subagent_type":"Explore","prompt":"I need to investigate a Kubernetes bug in the watch cache where DELETE events have incorrect resourceVersion. The codebase is at /workspace/kubernetes/.\n\nPlease find and read the following files:\n1. The watch cache implementation - likely at pkg/storage/cacher/ or similar\n2. The etcd3 watcher implementation - likely at pkg/storage/etcd3/ or similar\n3. Any filtering logic for namespace-scoped watches\n\nSpecifically look for:\n1. Code that sends DELETE events from watch cache with PrevObject but doesn't update resourceVersion\n2. How etcd3 watcher handles DELETE events (it reportedly copies the event resourceVersion onto the previous object)\n3. The watch cache filtering that converts MODIFIED events to DELETE events for namespace-scoped watches\n\nPlease read the full content of these key files:\n- pkg/storage/cacher/watch_cache.go or similar\n- pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go or similar\n- Any file with \"filter\" in name related to watches\n\nReport back the exact file paths, line numbers, and code snippets showing:\n1. Where the watch cache sends DELETE events without fixing resourceVersion\n2. Where etcd3 correctly handles DELETE events\n3. The full path from client-go informer to watch cache"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9467,"cache_read_input_tokens":7097,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9467},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e8a2b282-9c85-4d7e-a765-e2618887422f","uuid":"4ce158d2-97