{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FiKJsbnNguwfy2bbPPUcLo","type":"tool_result","content":"351\tfunc (wc *watchChan) prepareObjs(e *event) (curObj runtime.Object, oldObj runtime.Object, err error) {\n352\t\tif !e.isDeleted {\n353\t\t\tdata, _, err := wc.watcher.transformer.TransformFromStorage(e.value, authenticatedDataString(e.key))\n354\t\t\tif err != nil {\n355\t\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n356\t\t\t}\n357\t\t\tcurObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)\n358\t\t\tif err != nil {\n359\t\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n360\t\t\t}\n361\t\t}\n362\t\t// We need to decode prevValue, only if this is deletion event or\n363\t\t// the underlying filter doesn't accept all objects (otherwise we\n364\t\t// know that the filter for previous object will return true and\n365\t\t// we need the object only to compute whether it was filtered out\n366\t\t// before).\n367\t\tif len(e.prevValue) > 0 && (e.isDeleted || !wc.acceptAll()) {\n368\t\t\tdata, _, err := wc.watcher.transformer.TransformFromStorage(e.prevValue, authenticatedDataString(e.key))\n369\t\t\tif err != nil {\n370\t\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n371\t\t\t}\n372\t\t\t// Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd revision for the time at\n373\t\t\t// which it gets deleted.\n374\t\t\toldObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)\n375\t\t\tif err != nil {\n376\t\t\t\treturn nil, nil, err\n377\t\t\t}\n378\t\t}\n379\t\treturn curObj, oldObj, nil\n380\t}\n381\t\n382\tfunc decodeObj(codec runtime.Codec, versioner storage.Versioner, data []byte, rev int64) (_ runtime.Object, err error) {\n383\t\tobj, err := runtime.Decode(codec, []byte(data))\n384\t\tif err != nil {\n385\t\t\tif fatalOnDecodeError {\n386\t\t\t\t// catch watch decode error iff we caused it on\n387\t\t\t\t// purpose during a unit test\n388\t\t\t\tdefer testingDeferOnDecodeError()\n389\t\t\t\t// we are running in a test environment and thus an\n390\t\t\t\t// error here is due to a coder mistake if the defer\n391\t\t\t\t// does not catch it\n392\t\t\t\tpanic(err)\n393\t\t\t}\n394\t\t\treturn nil, err\n395\t\t}\n396\t\t// ensure resource version is set on the object we load from etcd\n397\t\tif err := versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev)); err != nil {\n398\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failure to version api object (%d) %#v: %v\", rev, obj, err)\n399\t\t}\n400\t\treturn obj, nil\n401\t}\n402\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Beb4TbnUESNeUmKMEDYctf","session_id":"e8a2b282-9c85-4d7e-a765-e2618887422f","uuid":"09340352-4ba5-4b31-b52f-d31540f40d7e","timestamp":"2026-04-01T00:38:39.444Z"}
