{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Beb4TbnUESNeUmKMEDYctf","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive report. I have all the information I need:\n\n## Bug Investigation Report: Kubernetes Watch Cache DELETE Events with Incorrect resourceVersion\n\nI have completed a thorough investigation of the Kubernetes watch cache implementation and identified the exact locations where the bug manifests. Here are my findings:\n\n---\n\n### KEY FILES IDENTIFIED\n\n1. **Watch Cache Implementation**\n   - `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go`\n\n2. **etcd3 Watcher Implementation**\n   - `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go`\n   - `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/event.go`\n\n3. **Cacher (Watch Request Handler)**\n   - `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`\n\n---\n\n### BUG LOCATION #1: Watch Cache DELETE Events Without resourceVersion Update\n\n**File:** `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go`\n\n**Lines 249-261 (watchCacheEvent creation in processEvent):**\n\n```go\nwatchCacheEvent := &watchCacheEvent{\n    Type:                 event.Type,\n    Object:               event.Object,\n    ObjLabels:            objLabels,\n    ObjFields:            objFields,\n    ObjUninitialized:     objUninitialized,\n    PrevObject:           prevObject,              // <-- ISSUE: PrevObject has OLD resourceVersion\n    PrevObjLabels:        prevObjLabels,\n    PrevObjFields:        prevObjFields,\n    PrevObjUninitialized: prevObjUninitialized,\n    Key:                  key,\n    ResourceVersion:      resourceVersion,        // <-- Current event's resourceVersion\n}\n```\n\n**The Problem:**\n- The `watchCacheEvent.ResourceVersion` field is set to the current event's resourceVersion (line 260)\n- However, when a DELETE event is sent, the `PrevObject` field (line 255) is the previous object retrieved from the internal store (line 243)\n- This `PrevObject` was stored with its own resourceVersion from when it was last seen, NOT the current DELETE event's resourceVersion\n- When the DELETE event is later sent to watchers via `cacher.go`, the `PrevObject` is sent to clients but with the wrong resourceVersion embedded in it\n\n---\n\n### BUG LOCATION #2: Cacher Sends DELETE with PrevObject (Wrong resourceVersion)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go`\n\n**Lines 875-894 (cacheWatcher.sendWatchCacheEvent):**\n\n```go\nfunc (c *cacheWatcher) sendWatchCacheEvent(event *watchCacheEvent) {\n    curObjPasses := event.Type != watch.Deleted && c.filter(event.Key, event.ObjLabels, event.ObjFields, event.ObjUninitialized)\n    oldObjPasses := false\n    if event.PrevObject != nil {\n        oldObjPasses = c.filter(event.Key, event.PrevObjLabels, event.PrevObjFields, event.PrevObjUninitialized)\n    }\n    if !curObjPasses && !oldObjPasses {\n        // Watcher is not interested in that object.\n        return\n    }\n\n    var watchEvent watch.Event\n    switch {\n    case curObjPasses && !oldObjPasses:\n        watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Added, Object: event.Object.DeepCopyObject()}\n    case curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n        watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Modified, Object: event.Object.DeepCopyObject()}\n    case !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses:\n        watchEvent = watch.Event{Type: watch.Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()}\n        // <-- ISSUE: For namespace-scoped watches with MODIFIED->DELETE conversion,\n        //     the PrevObject is sent but contains old resourceVersion\n    }\n```\n\n**The Critical Issue (Line 893):**\nWhen a MODIFIED event is converted to a DELETE event due to filtering (when `curObjPasses && !oldObjPasses` = false and `!curObjPasses && oldObjPasses` = true), the code sends `event.PrevObject` in the DELETE watch.Event. However, this `PrevObject` has the resourceVersion from when it was last updated, not the current event's resourceVersion.\n\n---\n\n### CORRECT BEHAVIOR IN etcd3 WATCHER\n\n**File:** `/workspace/kubernetes/staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go`\n\n**Lines 351-380 (prepareObjs) and 382-401 (decodeObj):**\n\nThe etcd3 watcher does this correctly:\n\n```go\nfunc (wc *watchChan) prepareObjs(e *event) (curObj runtime.Object, oldObj runtime.Object, err error) {\n    if !e.isDeleted {\n        // ... decode current value ...\n        curObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)\n    }\n    \n    if len(e.prevValue) > 0 && (e.isDeleted || !wc.acceptAll()) {\n        // ... decode previous value ...\n        // Note that this sends the *old* object with the etcd revision for the time at\n        // which it gets deleted.\n        oldObj, err = decodeObj(wc.watcher.codec, wc.watcher.versioner, data, e.rev)\n        // <-- CORRECT: e.rev is the DELETE event's revision, applied to oldObj\n    }\n    return curObj, oldObj, nil\n}\n\nfunc decodeObj(codec runtime.Codec, versioner storage.Versioner, data []byte, rev int64) (_ runtime.Object, err error) {\n    obj, err := runtime.Decode(codec, []byte(data))\n    // ensure resource version is set on the object we load from etcd\n    if err := versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev)); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failure to version api object (%d) %#v: %v\", rev, obj, err)\n    }\n    return obj, nil\n}\n```\n\n**Why etcd3 is correct:** Line 374 passes `e.rev` (the current DELETE event's revision) to `decodeObj`, which then calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` to set the correct resourceVersion on the old object.\n\n---\n\n### COMPLETE DATA FLOW\n\n1. **etcd3 WatchChan receives DELETE:**\n   - Event from etcd has revision `N` (the DELETE revision)\n   - Previous value is decoded with revision `N` (correct)\n   - Both curObj and oldObj get revision `N` set via `versioner.UpdateObject()`\n\n2. **Event sent to Cacher:**\n   - watch.Event is created with curObj or oldObj or synthetic event\n   - Both objects have revision `N`\n\n3. **Cacher receives via reflector:**\n   - Event is processed and stored in watchCache via `watchCache.Add/Update/Delete`\n   - watchCache creates watchCacheEvent with ResourceVersion = `N`\n   - PrevObject retrieved from internal store has OLD revision from last update\n\n4. **Cacher dispatches to watchers:**\n   - For namespace-scoped watches, MODIFIED can become DELETE\n   - When `!curObjPasses && oldObjPasses`, sends `event.PrevObject` \n   - But `event.PrevObject` has old resourceVersion (not `N`)\n\n5. **Client receives incorrect DELETE:**\n   - watch.Event type = Deleted\n   - Object.metadata.resourceVersion is outdated\n\n---\n\n### SUMMARY OF THE BUG\n\n| Component | Correct Behavior | Buggy Behavior |\n|-----------|------------------|----------------|\n| **etcd3 watcher** | oldObj gets DELETE event's revision `N` | N/A (works correctly) |\n| **watchCache** | Should update PrevObject to current ResourceVersion | Stores PrevObject with old resourceVersion |\n| **cacheWatcher** | Should send PrevObject with event's ResourceVersion | Sends PrevObject with cached resourceVersion |\n\nThe root cause is that **watchCache stores PrevObject with whatever resourceVersion it had in the store**, and **never updates it to match the current event's ResourceVersion**, even though the etcd3 layer correctly assigns the event's revision to it. This difference is lost when the object transitions from etcd3 to the in-memory watchCache."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e8a2b282-9c85-4d7e-a765-e2618887422f","uuid":"6985eac2-5f55-4059-8aee-e141107ffab5","timestamp":"2026-04-01T00:39:29.537Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to investigate a Kubernetes bug in the watch cache where DELETE events have incorrect resourceVe