ourceVersion M < N)\",\n    \"watchCacheEvent is created with ResourceVersion=N but PrevObject.metadata.resourceVersion=M (watch_cache.go:249-261) — no UpdateObject call to fix prevObject\",\n    \"cacher dispatches watchCacheEvent to all cacheWatchers via sendWatchCacheEvent (cacher.go:875)\",\n    \"Namespace-scoped filter: curObjPasses=false (object left namespace), oldObjPasses=true → falls into !curObjPasses && oldObjPasses branch (cacher.go:892)\",\n    \"Synthetic DELETE sent with watch.Event{Type: Deleted, Object: event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()} carrying metadata.resourceVersion=M (stale) (cacher.go:893)\",\n    \"client-go informer updates lastSyncResourceVersion to M\",\n    \"On watch reconnect, informer resumes from M — events between M and N may be re-delivered or events after N missed depending on API server resume semantics\"\n  ],\n  \"trigger_conditions\": [\n    \"Namespace-scoped watch via API server with watch cache enabled\",\n    \"Object in the watched namespace is modified so it no longer matches the watcher's filter (e.g., moved to a different namespace, labels changed to not match a label selector)\",\n    \"The watch cache converts the MODIFIED event to a synthetic DELETE for the scoped watcher\",\n    \"The watch connection drops and is re-established after the stale resourceVersion is recorded\"\n  ],\n  \"code_paths\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/watch_cache.go\",\n      \"function\": \"processEvent\",\n      \"line\": 217,\n      \"note\": \"Creates watchCacheEvent with PrevObject from store — missing versioner.UpdateObject(prevObject, resourceVersion)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/cacher.go\",\n      \"function\": \"sendWatchCacheEvent\",\n      \"line\": 892,\n      \"note\": \"!curObjPasses && oldObjPasses branch sends PrevObject without correcting its resourceVersion\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go\",\n      \"function\": \"prepareObjs\",\n      \"line\": 374,\n      \"note\": \"Correct: oldObj decoded with e.rev (DELETE revision) passed to decodeObj\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/watcher.go\",\n      \"function\": \"decodeObj\",\n      \"line\": 397,\n      \"note\": \"Correct: versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev)) stamps event revision onto decoded object\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go\",\n      \"function\": \"sendDelete\",\n      \"line\": 442,\n      \"note\": \"Correct: node.ModifiedIndex = res.Node.ModifiedIndex overwrites PrevNode index with DELETE event index before decoding\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd/etcd_watcher.go\",\n      \"function\": \"sendModify\",\n      \"line\": 400,\n      \"note\": \"Correct: versioner.UpdateObject(oldObj, res.Node.ModifiedIndex) stamps DELETE revision for filter-induced synthetic DELETEs\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"ownership\": \"API server storage layer — watch cache (pkg/storage/cacher.go and pkg/storage/watch_cache.go)\",\n  \"severity\": {\n    \"level\": \"high\",\n    \"rationale\": \"Causes client-go informers to silently miss events after a watch reconnect for any namespace-scoped watch where objects can leave the filter. This affects the majority of Kubernetes controllers (Deployment, ReplicaSet, StatefulSet, DaemonSet, etc.) and leads to stale controller state without any error surfaced. The issue is non-deterministic and only manifests on watch reconnect after the specific filter-conversion scenario, making it hard to detect in testing.\"\n  },\n  \"remediation\": {\n    \"approach\": \"In sendWatchCacheEvent (cacher.go:892-893), call versioner.UpdateObject on the DeepCopy of PrevObject before sending the DELETE event, using event.ResourceVersion as the revision. This mirrors the pattern in etcd3 watcher (decodeObj, line 397) 