{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019LGEJbmNGYi1HUUN6abnwu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both files have been written. Here's a summary of the findings:\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe bug is in two places in the watch cache layer:\n\n**1. `watch_cache.go:processEvent` (line 243)**\nWhen building a `watchCacheEvent`, `prevObject` is fetched from the in-memory store — it carries the resourceVersion from when it was last stored (`M`), not the current event's revision (`N`). No `versioner.UpdateObject` call is made to update it.\n\n**2. `cacher.go:sendWatchCacheEvent` (line 892–893)**\nWhen a namespace-scoped filter converts a MODIFIED event to a synthetic DELETE (`!curObjPasses && oldObjPasses`), it sends `event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()` — with the stale resourceVersion `M` — as the DELETE body.\n\n## Correct Reference Implementations\n\nBoth existing watchers fix this correctly:\n\n- **etcd3** (`etcd3/watcher.go:374,397`): `decodeObj(..., e.rev)` calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` with the DELETE event's revision.\n- **Legacy etcd** (`etcd/etcd_watcher.go:400,442`): `sendModify` calls `versioner.UpdateObject(oldObj, res.Node.ModifiedIndex)`; `sendDelete` overwrites `node.ModifiedIndex` before decoding.\n\n## Fix\n\nIn `cacher.go:sendWatchCacheEvent`, stamp the DELETE event's `event.ResourceVersion` onto the `PrevObject` copy before sending (mirroring the etcd3/legacy-etcd pattern)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":184,"cache_read_input_tokens":34632,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":184},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e8a2b282-9c85-4d7e-a765-e2618887422f","uuid":"2f957d8e-c537-41d7-833a-08a59d00cb28"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":215302,"duration_api_ms":214866,"num_turns":17,"result":"Both files have been written. Here's a summary of the findings:\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe bug is in two places in the watch cache layer:\n\n**1. `watch_cache.go:processEvent` (line 243)**\nWhen building a `watchCacheEvent`, `prevObject` is fetched from the in-memory store — it carries the resourceVersion from when it was last stored (`M`), not the current event's revision (`N`). No `versioner.UpdateObject` call is made to update it.\n\n**2. `cacher.go:sendWatchCacheEvent` (line 892–893)**\nWhen a namespace-scoped filter converts a MODIFIED event to a synthetic DELETE (`!curObjPasses && oldObjPasses`), it sends `event.PrevObject.DeepCopyObject()` — with the stale resourceVersion `M` — as the DELETE body.\n\n## Correct Reference Implementations\n\nBoth existing watchers fix this correctly:\n\n- **etcd3** (`etcd3/watcher.go:374,397`): `decodeObj(..., e.rev)` calls `versioner.UpdateObject(obj, uint64(rev))` with the DELETE event's revision.\n- **Legacy etcd** (`etcd/etcd_watcher.go:400,442`): `sendModify` calls `versioner.UpdateObject(oldObj, res.Node.ModifiedIndex)`; `sendDelete` overwrites `node.ModifiedIndex` before decoding.\n\n## Fix\n\nIn `cacher.go:sendWatchCacheEvent`, stamp the DELETE event's `event.ResourceVersion` onto the `PrevObject` copy before sending (mirroring the etcd3/legacy-etcd pattern).","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"e8a2b282-9c85-4d7e-a765-e2618887422f","total_cost_usd":0.45219569999999987,"usage":{"input_tokens":16,"cache_creation_input_tokens":27719,"cache_read_input_tokens":342061,"output_tokens":7204,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":27719,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":16,"outputTokens":7204,"cacheRea